oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Women on back porch with dogs
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of five women and three dogs on the back porch of the Grassmere home. The woman sitting on the right of the steps appears to be Leila Shute Tigert, and the woman holding a dog in the back appears to be Kate Emerson.

Leila Shute (1868-1952) was one of the four daughters of William and Lavinia Shute. She married Dr. Holland McTyeire Tigert (1880-1948) in approximately 1901. The Tigerts lived at Grassmere and Leila oversaw the running of the farm after her father died.
